# 🚗 Automotive Digital Twin Dashboard

## Overview
This project simulates an automotive ECU network using CAN communication concepts and visualizes real-time vehicle telemetry through an interactive dashboard.

## Demo
![Dashboard](dashboard.png)

## Features

- Real-time vehicle telemetry (Speed, RPM, Temperature)
- Live updating dashboard
- Fault detection (Overheat, High RPM)
- CAN message simulation (0x101, 0x102, 0x103)
- Multi-ECU system visualization

## Architecture
Laptop Simulation → CAN Data → Dashboard

## Tech Used
- Python
- Streamlit
- CAN simulation concepts

## Future Work
- Integrate STM32 hardware
- Real CAN communication
- Diagnostics module

## Roadmap
- Implement real CAN communication
- Add diagnostic protocols (UDS/OBD)
- Expand into full vehicle digital twin

## Why This Project Matters

This project demonstrates:
- Real-time embedded system thinking
- Automotive ECU communication concepts
- CAN-based data simulation
- System-level architecture design
